Aetna , Inc. ( NYSE : AET ) is an American diversified health care benefits company , providing a range of traditional and consumer directed health care insurance products and related services , including medical , pharmacy , dental , behavioral health , group life , long - term care , and disability plans , and medical management capabilities . It is the direct descendant of Aetna Insurance Company , of Hartford , Connecticut , which issued its first life insurance policy in 1850 , a full 30 years after it had been chartered to enter the business . Aetna merged with U.S. Healthcare in 1996 . It was one of only 11 companies to earn a 100 % score on the Human Rights Campaign Corporate Equality Index in 2002 , the first year of the survey . It has maintained this rating in 2003 and 2004 . Aetna covers health care , dental , pharmacy , group life , disability , and long - term care insurance and employee benefits. . In 2002 their stock was around $7 and today ( 2007 ) it is $55 . It was announced on January 4 2006 that Dr. Ronald Williams would succeed Dr. John W. Rowe as CEO as of February 14 , 2006 . Rowe will become Executive Chairman until he retires at the end of 2006 . Aetna corporate website , with a brief company history . 